<BLOCKQUOTE><BR>CLASS:&nbsp; Warrior
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP: very important<BR>Mana: not important<BR>Endurance: average importance<BR>AC: very important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen: below average importance.&nbsp; it's nice, but not something I go out of the way for<BR>Mana Regen: not important<BR>Endurance Regen: I wish.&nbsp; Would love to see endurence regen on gear.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength: and other stats--easy to cap, and as long as they are capped, more is not needed<BR></DIV>
<DIV>resists:&nbsp;&nbsp; Wish they meant more.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: Below average importance.<BR>Delay: All things being equal, I prefer slower delays, to avoid ripostes and damage shieds(DS only relevant to primary weapons)<BR>Damage: The more the better.&nbsp; Most of my agro comes from melee, the higher the damage, the more agro per swing.&nbsp; Massivly important.<BR>Range:&nbsp; Very minor importance.&nbsp; I use range attacks almost never.</DIV>
<DIV>Haste: Very important.&nbsp; Need more haste items in game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects: highly important.&nbsp; Agro from procs is big for warriors, and CE means more procs<BR>Shielding: Very important<BR>Stun Resist: Kinda important<BR>Strikethrough:&nbsp; not important<BR>Spell Shield: very important<BR>Avoidance: very important<BR>Accuracy: important<BR>DOT Shielding: very important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: important.&nbsp; Would be nice to see more items with skill mods<BR>Click Effects: very important<BR>Proc Effects: very very important.&nbsp; Static blow, anger, static blow, anger, static blow, anger...more of those.<BR>Worn Effects: variable<BR>Focus Effects: variable<BR></DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
				
